Italy's overall balance of payments showeda deficit of 3,211 billion lire in May compared with a surplusof 2,040 billion in April, provisional Bank of Italy figuresshow.    The May deficit compares with a surplus of 1,555 billionlire in the corresponding month of 1986.    For the first five months of 1987, the overall balance ofpayments showed a surplus of 299 billion lire against a deficitof 2,854 billion in the corresponding 1986 period. REUTER&#3;